The game will be played on Monday at the Olympic Stadium in Rome and is also expected to feature the world's current greatest player Lionel Messi alongside several 'all-star players'.

Argentina manager Gerardo Tata Martino and Arsenal's Arsene Wenger will select teams from a squad of 50 players from different religous backgrounds, including Roberto Baggio, a renowned Budhist, and Zinedine Zidane who professes Islam 

The two teams, named PUPI and SCHOLAS will be captained by Zanetti and Italy goalkeeper Gianluigi Buffon.

